---------------- 
Install Eclipse, Android SDK and Eclipse Android binding
---------------- 

Open Terminal window and type:
  - sudo yum -y install eclipse
(Eclipse Luna will be installed on Fedora 21 at Dec 2014)
  
Download SDK from page:
  https://developer.android.com
(If you have installed Android Studio, the Android SDK is already installed)

Start Eclipse, then select Help > Install new software
Click Add and insert:
  - http://download.eclipse.org/releases/luna/ or your version of Eclipse
  - https://dl-ssl.google.com/android/eclipse/ 
Restart Eclipse and Go to Window -> Preferences, click on Android and set SDK location to directory(e.g /home/user/Android/SDK)
Click Apply and OK.
Restart Eclipse


---------------- 
Optional JAVA Gnome Gtk bind for Eclipse
---------------- 

Open Terminal window and type:
sudo yum install libjava-gnome-java

In Eclipse, to compile with Java-Gnome bindings:
  - Select your Java App > Properties 
  - Java Build Path > Libraries > Add External JARs
  - Choose 64 Bit Environment --> /usr/lib64/java-gnome/gtk.jar
           32 Bit Environment --> /usr/lib/java-gnome/gtk.jar
           
           
All references at http://java-gnome.sourceforge.net

